{"article_id":"GI2jtLd5lrNb3M6D","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The president will announces the end of the NSA 's telephone metadata program .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Obama revamps U.S. surveillance","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"President Barack Obama on Friday said","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"the United States will stop collecting and storing telephone metadata","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"but delivered a stern defense of the nation ' s intelligence gathering practices .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Obama announced the changes in the National Security Agency ' s telephone metadata program during a speech at the Justice Department ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"calling for an end to the government ' s practice","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"of storing a huge trove of information on Americans ' telephone calls .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"\" I believe","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"we need a new approach , \"","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"\" I am therefore ordering a transition","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that will end the Section 215 bulk metadata program","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"as it currently exists ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"and establish a mechanism","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"that preserves the capabilities","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"we need","depth":13},{"id":17,"text":"without the government holding this bulk metadata . \"","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"The reforms are the most substantial public response by the White House to criticism at home and abroad over the scope of U.S. surveillance activities","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"revealed in documents","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"leaked by former NSA contractor Edward Snowden .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"Obama made the case","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that U.S. intelligence officials have not broken the law","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"or spied on the calls or e-mails of \" ordinary people . \"","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"\" In an extraordinarily difficult job , one","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"in which actions are second-guessed ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"success is unreported ,","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"and failure can be catastrophic ,","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"the men and women of the intelligence community ,","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"including the NSA ,","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"consistently follow protocols","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"designed to protect the privacy of ordinary people , \"","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"\" They are not abusing authorities","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"in order to listen to your private phone calls ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"or read your emails . \"","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"And yet Obama said","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"the United States will not halt intelligence-gathering activities","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"while the global threats remain .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"foreign governments","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"- without naming any -","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"continue trying to hack into U.S. government data .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"For this reason ,","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Obama said ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"mobile phones are not allowed inside the White House Situation Room .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"\" We can not unilaterally disarm our intelligence agencies , \"","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Obama said .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"\" We know","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"that the intelligence services of other countries","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"- including some","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"who feign surprise over the Snowden disclosures -","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"are constantly probing our government and private sector networks ,","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"and accelerating programs","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"to listen to our conversations ,","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"intercept our emails ,","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"or compromise our systems . \"","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"Obama ' s proposal pushes in the direction","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"of keeping the call data in the private sector :","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"either with phone companies themselves or a third-party","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"which would pool data from all companies .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"He also raised the possibility","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"that other intelligence agency capabilities might be able to replace the program .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Obama asked Attorney General Eric Holder and intelligence officials to come up with a detailed plan by March 28","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"for how to maintain the government ' s ability","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"to tap into the calling data .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"In the meantime , Obama said","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"every government search of telecommunications data will require review by the FISA court .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Until now , NSA personnel have been able to request the data","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"based on a \" reasonable , articulable suspicion \"","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"that phone numbers are tied to terrorist activity .","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"However , no judge routinely reviewed those queries","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"either before or after they were made .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"The president declared","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"that the government will no longer access phone records","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"more than two people removed from an individual","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"officials are monitoring ,","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"down from three people","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"removed under existing court orders .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"Obama is also asking Congress to create a panel of public advocates","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"that will monitor the FISA court process .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"Obama has gone to significant lengths","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"to calm overseas anger about the U.S. monitoring of foreign citizens , particularly foreign leaders","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"whose private cell phones had been monitored by the NSA ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"according to documents","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"leaked by Snowden .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"Though Obama acknowledged Snowden by name ,","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"he said","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"he is \" not going to dwell on Mr. Snowden ' s actions or motivations . \"","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"\" If any individual","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"who objects to government policy","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"can take it in their own hands","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"to publicly disclose classified information ,","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"then we will never be able to keep our people safe ,","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"or conduct foreign policy , \"","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"Obama said .","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"\" Moreover , the sensational way","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"in which these disclosures have come out","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"has often shed more heat than light ,","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"while revealing methods to our adversaries","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"that could impact our operations in ways","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"that we may not fully understand for years to come . \"","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"And yet Obama criticized foreign governments","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"that have criticized the United States","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"after the Snowden leaks","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"while privately acknowledging","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"the U.S. has a responsibility","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"to keep the world safe .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"\" A number of countries ,","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"including some","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"who have loudly criticized the NSA ,","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"privately acknowledge","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"that America has special responsibilities as the world ' s only superpower , \"","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"Obama said ,","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"adding","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"that some of those countries \" themselves have relied on the information","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"we obtain","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"to protect their own people . \"","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"Included in the directive","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"Obama is issuing","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"is language","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"that makes clear","depth":6},{"id":122,"text":"the United States \" does not use signals intelligence","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"to indiscriminately collect \" foreigners ' email and phone data ,","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"a senior administration official told reporters earlier Friday .","depth":4},{"id":125,"text":"Snowden ' s documents showed","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"the NSA had access to personal cell phone calls of a host of foreign leaders ,","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"including German Chancellor Angela Merkel .","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"Obama didn ' t mention Merkel during the speech ,","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"but did make reference to \" totalitarian states like East Germany , \"","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"where Merkel was raised .","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"\" People around the world","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"- regardless of their nationality -","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"should know","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"that the United States is not spying on ordinary people","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"who don ' t threaten our national security ,","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"and that we take their privacy concerns into account , \"","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"Obama said .","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"\" This applies to foreign leaders as well . \"","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":277,"left":140,"right":276,"relation":"organization","nuclearity